  <strong>2025-02-15</strong> – <a href="https://github.com/insin/control-panel-for-twitter">control-panel-for-twitter</a> <a href="https://github.com/insin/control-panel-for-twitter/releases/tag/v4.8.0">v4.8.0</a>
  <div><em>Browser extension which gives you more control over your Twitter timeline and adds missing features and UI improvements - available for desktop and mobile browsers</em></div>
  <details><summary>v4.8.0 release notes</summary><p>Visit the <a href="https://soitis.dev/control-panel-for-twitter" rel="nofollow">Control Panel for Twitter website</a> for installation links, more information about the extension, and FAQs. Follow <a href="https://twitter.com/ControlPanelFT" rel="nofollow">@ControlPanelFT</a> on Twitter or <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/soitis.dev" rel="nofollow">@soitis.dev</a> on Bluesky for updates.</p>
<h2>Changes</h2>
<ul>
<li>Added an option to redirect from x.com to twitter.com
<ul>
<li>If you're logged out of twitter.com, you will be redirected to the login page to avoid an infinite redirection loop</li>
<li>Note: this redirect will only work for as a long as Twitter supports the ?mx=1 query parameter they added as part of the migration to x.com</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Added automatically closing the new Premium upsell modal which sometimes appears after submitting a new Tweet on desktop</li>
<li>Added an option to hide the main Compose Tweet button</li>
<li>Added a Custom CSS option to the Experiments section</li>
<li>Added display of the version number you're using to the options page</li>
<li>Fixed the option for defaulting "Sort replies by"
<ul>
<li>Note: on mobile, Twitter appear to have broken their own UI for changing sorting, so if you use this option you won't be able to change reply sorting while looking at a Tweet thread</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Fixed hiding the "Edit" upsell in the menu on your own recent Tweets</li>
</ul>
